{"questionId":"22462053","questionHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>arg</mi><mo> </mo><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>θ</mi></math>;</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>arg</mi><mo> </mo><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>arctan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>arg</mi><mo> </mo><mi>z</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>uses <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math> in the numerator and any double angle identity for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>θ</mi></math> in the denominator&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>arg</mi><mo> </mo><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>arctan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>arg</mi><mo> </mo><mi>z</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xml